- take the lastest flyspray and install it somewhere in your filesystem
- create a symlink to your BTS module
  ln -s [flyspray] [e-venement]/bts/
- create the flyspray schema in your e-venement's database
  psql [your database]
  CREATE SCHEMA flyspray;
- dump the initial schema
  pg_restore -d [your database] sql/flyspray.pgdump
- patch your database
  psql [your database] < [e-venement]/bts/sql/init.sql
- patch your flyspray release
  cd [flyspray]
  patch -p1 < [e-venement]/bts/sql/flyspray_vanilla-evenement.diff
- install and configure the flyspray.conf.php file in [flyspray]
  nano [flyspray]/flyspray.conf.php
- edit your configuration file and adapt your cookiesalt parameter
  to be the same you've got in your flyspray's configuration file
- this is done
- add your users to the BTS using the global configuration interface
  http://[e-venement]/def/
  http://[e-venement]/bts/def/
- update your flyspray's tables "fly_users_private" and "fly_users_in_group"
  to adapt the user_id to your e-venement's admin account.id... for this, you
  can edit the [e-venement]/bts/sql/user_update.sql file to the necessary
  values and then :
  psql [your database] < [e-venement]/bts/sql/user_update.sql
- finished !! enjoy ! and have a look into flyspray's content before telling
  everyone "it's ok"... and link the needed people to your new module
